"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-07-20-paris-2024-olympics-chelsea-recall-ugochukwu-from-frances-squad\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Chelsea have recalled midfielder, Lesley Ugochukwu from France's squad for the Paris 2024 Olympics.  This is coming less than a week before the Paris 2024 Olympics kicks-off in France.  Ugochukwu did not make France's final 18-man squad.  But the 20-year-old had remained with France coach, Thierry Henry's side as one of four replacement players.  These replacements can play at the competition at any time should one of the 18 squad members get injured.  However, the French Football Federation announced in a statement on Friday that Chelsea had recalled their player  \\\"Lesley Ugochukwu leaves the Olympic selection,\\\" the statement read.  \\\"The midfielder is leaving the French Olympic Team this Friday, July 19, and will not be among the reserves for the Paris 2024 Olympic tournament.\\\"  Olympics 2024: Jamaican athlete drags Federation to CAS  EPL: They have courage - Ferguson names two players who represent 'heart and soul' of Man Utd  EPL: Chelsea take decision on Rosenior after 3-0 defeat to Everton  EPL: Chelsea players not interested in playing football - Liverpool legend, Nicol  EPL: 'You will be highly disappointed' - Gary Cahill slams Chelsea goalkeeper, Sanchez  EPL: Why we beat Chelsea 3-0 - Everton manager David Moyes  EPL: Rooney, Alan Shearer name signings Chelsea need to compete for title  UK, France, Germany 'under threat' from Iranian missiles - Israel  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"